{
  "text": "One such family of decentralized collision avoidance algorithms is velocity obstacles [CITATION_1] . In such techniques, trajectories are planned in the velocity space [CITATION_2] . These methods have also been extended to higher order dynamics [CITATION_3] and for high speed avoidance [CITATION_4] . Detrimentally, these methods require a reference velocity to be known.",
  "correct_citation": {
